			"blocks": {
				"cat-how": { "type": "category", "settings": { "title": "How it works" } },
				"q-how-1": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "How it works", "question": "How does the aira nasal strip work?", "answer": "<p>aira uses a lightweight magnetic strip that gently opens your nasal passages from the outside. Two small adhesive tabs sit on either side of your nose, and the magnetic bridge connects them — creating a soft, outward pull that widens your airway instantly.</p><p>No drugs, no intrusion, no discomfort. Just cleaner, more comfortable breathing from the moment you put it on.</p>" } },
				"q-how-2": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "How it works", "question": "How is aira different from regular nasal strips?", "answer": "<p>Standard nasal strips use adhesive alone to pull your nose open. That works early in the night, but the adhesive weakens over time — which is why they often peel by morning.</p><p>aira separates those two jobs: the magnetic strip handles the structural opening, and the tabs just hold it in place. Stronger hold, gentler on your skin, and breathing that stays consistent through the night rather than fading.</p>" } },
				"q-how-3": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "How it works", "question": "Will it help with my snoring?", "answer": "<p>For most people, yes. When your nose is properly open, your body defaults to nasal breathing instead of mouth breathing — and it's the mouth breathing that causes the soft-tissue vibration behind most snoring.</p><p>We hear from a lot of customers that their partner noticed the improvement before they did.</p>" } },

				"cat-kit": { "type": "category", "settings": { "title": "The kit & materials" } },
				"q-kit-1": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "The kit & materials", "question": "What's in the aira kit?", "answer": "<p>Four magnetic strip sizes (L1–L4), a pack of 30 adhesive tab pairs, and an application guide. The strips are reusable — you only replace the tabs as you go. Everything you need to find your fit and get started is in the kit.</p>" } },
				"q-kit-2": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "The kit & materials", "question": "How long does the strip last?", "answer": "<p>The magnetic strip itself lasts months — it's reusable. What you need to replace are the adhesive tabs, one pair per night. They come in packs of 30, 60, or 90 pairs, so your ongoing cost is just the tabs, not the whole kit every time.</p>" } },
				"q-kit-3": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "The kit & materials", "question": "Is it safe for sensitive skin?", "answer": "<p>The adhesive tabs are medical-grade and specifically designed to minimize irritation. They come off cleanly in the morning without pulling your skin. If your skin is particularly sensitive, you can do a small patch test on your first night — but most people with sensitive skin have no issues.</p>" } },

				"cat-size": { "type": "category", "settings": { "title": "Sizing & fit" } },
				"q-size-1": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "Sizing & fit", "question": "How do I find the right size?", "answer": "<p>The kit includes four strip sizes: L1–L4. A good fit means the strip's ends rest just on the outer edges of your nostrils without pressing them inward. If you're in between sizes, some people size up for workouts and use a smaller size for sleep.</p>" } },

				"cat-use": { "type": "category", "settings": { "title": "Using aira" } },
				"q-use-1": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "Using aira", "question": "How do I apply it?", "answer": "<p>Clean, dry skin is the one thing that actually matters — it's the step most people rush, and it's why tabs sometimes don't hold. Stick one tab on either side of your nose, on the flat area just outside your nostrils, then connect the magnetic bridge between them.</p><p>The guide in the kit has visuals, and most people get the hang of it within the first two or three nights.</p>" } },
				"q-use-2": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "Using aira", "question": "Is it comfortable to sleep with? What if it falls off?", "answer": "<p>Most people stop noticing it within a few minutes of putting it on. The strip is under 2 grams and sits flat against your skin. The adhesive is medical-grade, designed to hold through a full night — including if you move around a lot.</p><p>If it shifts, it's almost always a skin-prep issue: the tabs need clean, dry skin to grip properly. The kit comes with an application guide that covers this.</p>" } },
				"q-use-3": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "Using aira", "question": "How quickly will I notice a difference?", "answer": "<p>The opening in your airway is immediate — you'll feel it the moment you put it on. For snoring, give it a few nights. If you've been a mouth-breather for years, your body takes a little time to settle into nasal breathing as its default. A week is a fair window to judge it properly.</p>" } },
				"q-use-4": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "Using aira", "question": "What if the strip doesn't stick properly?", "answer": "<p>It's almost always a skin-prep issue. Make sure your nose is completely clean and dry before applying — no moisturizer, no sweat, no residue from a previous strip. If your skin is naturally oily, a quick wipe with a dry tissue right before application will help. The tabs are medical-grade adhesive, so when the prep is right, they hold reliably.</p>" } },
				"q-use-5": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "Using aira", "question": "Can I use it during exercise?", "answer": "<p>Yes — and it actually works particularly well for this. The tabs are sweat-resistant and stay put through running, cycling, or anything high-intensity. Nasal breathing during exercise is worth getting right: it improves oxygen uptake and helps regulate your heart rate.</p>" } },

				"cat-orders": { "type": "category", "settings": { "title": "Orders & shipping" } },
				"q-ord-1": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "Orders & shipping", "question": "Do you ship to the GCC?", "answer": "<p>Yes — we ship to the UAE, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, Bahrain, Qatar, and Oman. Most orders arrive in 3–5 business days.</p>" } },
				"q-ord-2": { "type": "faq_item", "settings": { "category": "Orders & shipping", "question": "Do you have a return policy?", "answer": "<p>We stand behind every product we make. Try aira for 30 days — if you're not happy with your purchase for any reason, contact us at <a href=\"mailto:contact@aira-breathing.com\">contact@aira-breathing.com</a> within 30 days of delivery and we'll guide you through the return process.</p>" } }
